<p>Chen Ning Yang, the Chinese-American theoretical physicist, died in Beijing on October 18 at age 103 after an illness, according to China’s state news agency Xinhua [reuters.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. He shared the 1957 Nobel Prize in Physics with Tsung-Dao Lee and was widely recognized for pioneering work on symmetry principles in particle physics and contributions to statistical mechanics [reuters.com#1][theguardian.com#1][bbc.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/KHoZ2OOmiEojU2kowhLxIA7G9FBLVxRS1Dri1Vmuye5JsiILnrISDrIPaHEOM75vMQEUBCEtPy3p4ATl2DdgeK8ICi1fCsElh97EiLuAysxYjQHoPUz04DaATuYBtojSYeu76JwbSVpyHcX4x14hlCYkk9K0lJAf8gWXVlhneQ' alt='Nobel laureate Chen Ning Yang during a public appearance.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Early life: He was born in Hefei, Anhui province, in 1922 [theguardian.com#1][reuters.com#1].</li><li>Overseas study: He moved to the United States in the 1940s for academic studies and later held teaching positions [ndtv.com#1].</li><li>Landmark theory: In 1954 he and Robert Mills co-authored the Yang–Mills equations, a framework describing three of nature’s fundamental forces [scmp.com#1].</li><li>Sparse details: State media noted he died of illness but did not provide additional information [scmp.com#1][thehindu.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/oct/18/chen-ning-yang-chinese-american-physicist-and-nobel-laureate-dies-at-103'>Chen Ning Yang, Chinese-American physicist and Nobel laureate, dies at 103</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/chinese-nobel-prize-winning-physicist-chen-ning-yang-126640875'>Chinese Nobel Prize-winning physicist Chen Ning Yang dies at 103</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/nobel-prize-winner-chinese-physicist-chen-ning-yang-dies-at-103-9477931#publisher=newsstand'>Nobel Prize Winner, Chinese Physicist Chen-Ning Yang, Dies At 103</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https